@node intro "Introduction"

Once Upon A Time..
------------------

I am a member of a National Lottery Syndicate (who have won very little! -
so far ;)).  I was fed up of checking the numbers of 8 people every week as
the novelty wore off.  So I decided to knock up a simple little program to
tell me if the numbers my syndicate had chosen were the <winning ones>.

I then suddenly realised that this program saves a lot of time to syndicate
members who have to trudge through their friends/colleagues numbers (Often
who never check themselves!).  So I started to expand the program by giving
it a GUI via gadtools.  After this I started adding a few features here
there and everywhere until I had a reasonable looking package.  The result
of which you can roughly see in this demo version I have distributed.

Demo Version Restrictions..
---------------------------

1. The bottom window in the shareware version has a number of novel 
   ideas such as syndicate forecasts, history analysis, member analysis
   etc etc.  But in this CRIPPLED PD DEMO RELEASE you will just see 
   a blatant advert!. 

2. You will also notice that in the first window the buttons 'EDIT' &
   'DELETE' are on their own!.  This is because this CRIPPLED version does
   not allow you to see the other buttons such as :>
	'INSERT' - Inserts a new member at chosen location.
	'NEW'    - Brings up a requester to clear database and set number of
                   members (Up To Maximimum of 300)

3. Menus aswell as HOTKEYS on the demo version are also few and far between

4. There are also many little features missing from this version such as:>
	
	a) When the user updates the chart they can specify whether another
	   small window pops up and tells you any winning entries.

	b) Estimates prize money of 4 or more winning lottery balls.

	c) More sensible tabs when editing gadgets (i.e not user number 6
	   backwards to user number 1!.

	d) Saving of program config for attributes like (a), default
	   syndicate prefs etc etc etc.

5. etc etc


ABOUT THE PROGRAMMER
--------------------

I am 20 years old and first started programming on the BBC Computer when I
was about 10.  The first game I wrote was a PACMAN clone and then I did a
sports game like the summer games compilations.  The first computer i ever 
owned myself though was the C64 which admitley was just a games machine and
i never tried art or assembly programming, although i did do quite a bit of
music on it. I bought my first Amiga 500 in 1988/1989 because my friend had 
one and it blew away my C64! (He kept showing me Shadow Of the Beast and the
Batmobile Part in Batman).  After getting the A500 I did the odd bit of
programming here and there such as for my A Level computer studies which
took a long time! - the program ended up 5000 lines long - although it was
a paint program with image effects etc!.  I may even release it for A500
users if they wish so as Public Domain or as a bonus for buying 'Syndicate
Pro_v1.00'.

After my 'A' levels I was put off programming and did not really do many 
projects and concentrated on making music via Music X and protracker.
After finding that my music talent was about 43%! one of my friends got me
interested in raytracing via Real3d v1.4 which was by now at rock bottom
price.  After a time I have never looked back and am mainly interested in
creating 3D graphics for video/home (bigger productions perhaps in the
future?). So you could call this my 'first' program release.  Anyway time
to render I suppose! see ya all later!


Finally
-------

I hope you enjoy this program and find it useful as I do.  Just would like 
to say that the AMIGA is the best home computer around and even beats the PC 
at most video applications. 


@endnode

