@node howtouse "How To Use Syndicate Professional (CRIPPLED PD DEMO VERSION)"
How to use:
-----------

	Easy GUI makes it quite logical to use!.  But below are the main 
	listed features and how to use them.

	THE PD CRIPPLED DEMO VERSION has 4 Windows
	------------------------------------------

	The Following points explain what each of the windows do/contain:>


	SYNDICATE MEMBERS (window)
	--------------------------

	a) People's names in the syndicate can be customised by clicking on
	   'edit' after selecting an entry in the gadgetlist.

	b) The 'delete' gadget will delete the current selected entry.

	c) The scroll gadget shows you the syndicate members

	d) The 6 six gadgets at the bottom of the window let you enter your
	   own lottery numbers.  Please note that the numbers are only
	   saved if you press tab or return.


	WINNING LOTTERY NUMBERS
	-----------------------
	
	a) There are 6 gadgets at the top of the window which is where the
	   JACKPOT lottery numbers are updated while watching the LIVE 
	   JACKPOT DRAW on television.

	b) The other bonus cycle gadget is for the last bonus number and
	   after updating this the 6 JACKPOT numbers will be sorted
	   numerically.

	c) The last gadget in this window is the 'Check Numbers' which will
	   go and look at the syndicate members numbers and tell you what 
	   you have achieved!

	
	NATIONAL LOTTERY RESULTS
	------------------------

	a) The list gadget on the left is updated when the 'Check Numbers'
	   button is pressed.  It tells you who won what, i.e if they lost
	   or won a prize etc.  It is more useful with small syndicates.

	b) The bar graph is a visual way of telling you if you have won
	   anything worthwhile.  This is ideal in the shareware version if 
	   you have a syndicate of 100 people or so because you can quite
	   clearly see the number of winning entries.


	WHY SHOULD YOU REGISTER
	-----------------------
	
	Well ....ermm...ermm.. is this a blatant reminder/advert/self-indulgence 
	or what!.  If you like the program and want me to continue
	producing software for the AMIGA then I would like some feedback.
	If you have any ideas for programs then do not hesitate to contact me at 
	my friends email address.  Registering also tells me that people
	like my program and that I should continue releasing AMIGA shareware
	programs, otherwise new software dissappears........


	P.S 
	
	Dear Pirate,
			Hmmmmm... well as this program is going shareware
	you are bound to 'release' it are'nt you?.  Have you ever stopped
	and thought about what piracy does to NEW AMIGA software?...  No? 
	well perhaps when all developers start making very little money 
	on the AMIGA and then look at other platforms (namely the PC) and 
	start to make more money then they will abandon the AMIGA.  

	Personally I would rather give up computing if the future depends 
	on the boring archaic PC.  Support the AMIGA and you will be
	rewarded.
	
	yours 
	S.R

	....
